SIMPLE: secundine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secundine
<hw>Sec"un*dine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>secondine</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
second coat, or integument, of an ovule, lying within the
primine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In the ripened seed the primine and secundine are
usually united to form the testa, or outer seed coat. When they remain
distinct the secundine becomes the mesosperm, as in the castor
bean.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>secondines</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
afterbirth, or placenta and membranes; -- generally used in the
plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secundo-geniture</ent>⟦br⟧
